    {"problem": "Given a set of distinct integers, return all possible subsets (the power set).", "reasoning": "Backtracking. At each index, we have two choices: include nums[i] or skip. Recurse to next index. When i == len(nums), add current subset to result. O(2^n) time.", "code": "def subsets(nums: list[int]) -> list[list[int]]:\n    res = []\n    def backtrack(i, path):\n        if i == len(nums):\n            res.append(path[:])\n            return\n        backtrack(i + 1, path)\n        path.append(nums[i])\n        backtrack(i + 1, path)\n        path.pop()\n    backtrack(0, [])\n    return res"},
